Observations :¶

  • Experience and Age are strongly correlated
  • One outlier in the zip code (certainly a false data)
  • Income is skrewed
  • Mortgage is highly screwed (bi-mode)
  • 106 people has zero credit card spending per month --> not possible
  • Most people do not have CD account and Seniorities Account
  • There is a linear treshold in the income above which the value of house mortgage is not exceeded
  • ZIP code won't be considered as categorical data since unique values are multiple: we can consider it as continuous numerical data

Interpretation :¶

  • Pseudo R^2 = 0.661 --> 66% of the uncertainty of the intercept is explained by the full model
  • If we consider a significance value of 5%, the important factors for the model are: Income, CCAvg, Family_3, Family_4, Education_2, Education_3

6. Business Insight¶

In this project, we want to maximize the number of customer buying personal loans. THe False Positive (predicting that a customer will buy a personal loan but won't) will consequenlty cost more than the False Negative. The Precision is the performance measure we want to maximize.

Here, the precision is 0.457 only, although the ROC AUC is ~89%. It is explained by the fact that we do not have enough samples from the past experience with customers who have already bought a loan. The target variable is highly unbalanced. Consequently, the accuracy of the model is based mainly on the prediction of the customers who won't buy a personal loan. This may not be what the bank is expecting and aditional data for customers buying a personal loan should be collected.
